==English==
===Etymology===
From ''[[360°]]'', the number of degrees in a full [[rotation]], + ''[[backflip]]'', the class maneuvers that begin similarly.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[360]] [[backflip]]}}

# a [[maneuver]] in various [[sport]]s (such as [[skateboarding]]) in which the player [[flip]]s [[backwards]], rotates a full turn, and finishes travelling in the original direction